review_comments.body:
I'd suggest doing first initializing the all properties of `map` then set the necessary columns to avoid issues when a new property gets added and for the ease of reading; i.e.:

``` c
*map = (yoml_t){YOML_TYPE_MAPPING};
if (node->filename != NULL)
    map->filename = h2o_strdup(node->filename).base;
...
```

Note also that you should use `h2o_strdup` in place of `strdup` for the same reasons we use `h2o_mem_alloc` in place of `malloc`.

